  • dresses for women

    This season's women's dresses are storming into women's wardrobes, featuring simple, fresh and delicate cuts as well as bold and edgy alternatives with a fierce energy. Short dresses are presented in a variety of styles offering a touch of freshness to the most sophisticated outfits, alternatives for casual looks and even stylish options for any festive event. ZARA's long dresses in sheer fabrics are romantic and flowing, while those in more structured materials convey finesse and adapt to special occasions. As a symbol of timeless sophistication, ZARA includes the iconic short black dress. And of course there are plenty of light options, such as white party dresses, which create on-trend looks with ethereal touches. From boho to sophisticated, the collection of women's dresses gives each look a unique style and personality.

ZARA Dresses for This Season

ZARA's dress edit features the latest new arrivals as well as timeless designs which never go wrong. The collection ranges from elegant short evening dresses and versatile printed mini dresses to long dresses to pair with trainers. Models from the extensive ZARA women's party collection also fall into this category, featuring short and long party dresses in an ample colour palette. In this edition, white party dresses which breathe modernity and style are presented alongside many other must-have colours such as black and dark blue as well as bright shades and printed options. ZARA's short dresses include both classic and on-trend styles. The short black dress, also known as little black dress, is an emblematic garment basic for any woman's wardrobe. One of its many qualities is not only the great potential in terms of versatility; it is a piece that exudes unpretentious elegance wherever it goes. For a look worthy of the most demanding dress codes, such a dress paired with a blazer is all the invitation one needs. If you prefer an outfit with a more vivid but equally foolproof colour, a blue dress or a green dress is the answer. For a brighter and more contemporary look, the ideal choice is a pink dress or a short white dress. In addition, there are plenty of options with cheerful prints, such as short floral dresses, an alternative that adds a positive note to any footwear and accessory with which they are combined. Fabrics can also add great sophistication to a piece. A mini dress with embroidered details is a very elaborate garment, made with materials that take it to the next level of style. Pair it with a pair of stand-out sandals for an impeccable look, but even tall boots with a short dress create an interesting and on-trend contrast effect, especially when worn with heels. In the middle of the spectrum ZARA presents the midi dress. Thanks to their length, neither too short nor too long, ZARA's midi dresses give a flattering silhouette and are perfect for showing off a pair of shoes to make a statement. Depending on the material, there are flowy options such as linen that allow total freedom of movement and provide a fresh feel, and others in robust fabrics such as leather that flatter the body, outlining its profile, giving off a sophisticated yet subtle sultry vibe. The maxi styles are presented in both romantic as well as sophisticated and cosmopolitan styles. Among the most bohemian options are long dresses with boots and long dresses with ankle boots. Conversely, there' s nothing like a long dress with trainers or a long dress with a blazer for an outfit that radiates modern urban energy, whether it's casual or more formal.

Your Privacy

Cookies and other similar technologies are an essential part of how our Platform works. The main goal of cookies is to make your browsing experience easier and more efficient and to improve our services and the Platform itself. Likewise, we use cookies to show you targeted advertising when you visit third-party websites and apps. Here, you will find all the information on the cookies we use. Furthermore, you will be able to activate and/or deactivate them according to your preferences, except for any cookies that are strictly necessary for the functioning of the Platform. Keep in mind that blocking certain cookies may affect your experience on the Platform, as well as its functioning. For more information, please consult our
Cookie Policy

Strictly necessary cookies

Always Active

These cookies are necessary for the correct functioning of the Platform, and they cannot be deactivated on our systems. Generally speaking, they are configured to respond to actions made by you when requesting services, such as adjusting your privacy preferences, logging in to your account or filling out forms. You can configure your browser to block these cookies or alert you when they are present; however, some parts of the platform will not work without them.

Analysis cookies

Active

These cookies allow us to analyze the number of visits and sources of traffic in order to measure and improve the performance of our Platform. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular, and how many people visit the website. If you do not allow these cookies, we will not know when you visited our Platform. To turn these cookies on or off toggle the button above. "Active" means these cookies can be used. "Inactive" means these cookies cannot be used.

Functionality or customisation cookies

"Inactive" means these cookies cannot be used.
